# TODO: Fix openrouter model patching in Hermes Docker Stack
#
# Context: The Hermes gateway fails with "No models provided" because the openrouter model list is not being added to _PROVIDER_MODELS in models.py.
#
# Root cause:
# - patch_providers.py uses MARKER = "openrouter" which matches other strings in models.py (e.g., provider labels)
# - This causes the idempotency check to skip the patch even though the _PROVIDER_MODELS key doesn't exist
# - The model list was also changed to use openrouter/ prefix which is incorrect
#
# Fix: Tighten the marker, restore correct model IDs, and add substitution verification
#
# Builder: This todo is self-contained. All context and steps are included.

## Task 1 — Fix patch_providers.py

### File: hermes/scripts/patch_providers.py

### Current (broken)
```python
MARKER = "openrouter"

MODELS = """\
    \"openrouter\": [
        \"openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash\",\
        \"x-ai/grok-4.3\",\
        \"minimax/minimax-m2.7\",\
        \"google/gemini-3-pro-preview\",\
    ],\
"""
```

### Replace with
```python
MARKER = '"openrouter": ['  # Exact key pattern to avoid false positives

MODELS = """\
    \"openrouter\": [
        \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\",\
        \"x-ai/grok-4.3\",\
        \"minimax/minimax-m2.7\",\
        \"google/gemini-3-pro-preview\",\
    ],\
"""
```

### Add verification
After the `re.sub` call, add:
```python
    if content == patched:
        print(f"ERROR: regex did not match in {TARGET} - no substitution made", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1
```

This ensures the patch actually applied.

## Task2 — Verify build

```bash
docker compose build --no-cache hermes
```

Then inspect the built image:
```bash
docker run --rm --entrypoint cat mps-ailab-hermes /opt/hermes/hermes_cli/models.py | grep -A10 '"openrouter": ['
```

Expected output:
```
    "openrouter": [
        "deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro",
        "x-ai/grok-4.3",
        "minimax/minimax-m2.7",
        "google/gemini-3-pro-preview",
    ],
```

## Task3 — Verify runtime

```bash
docker compose up -d hermes
docker compose exec hermes cat /home/hermes/.hermes/config.yaml | grep -A3 model
```

Expected output:
```
model:
  provider: openrouter
  name: deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro
  base_url: https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
```

Then check logs:
```bash
docker compose logs --tail=100 hermes | grep -i "No models provided"
```
Expected: no output (no error)

## Task4 — Commit

```bash
git add hermes/scripts/patch_providers.py
git commit -m "fix: tighten openrouter patch marker and restore correct model IDs"
git push
```

